<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1825] Configurations of delayed components are not deactivated if not used any more</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1825</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Declarative Service specification Section 112.5.4, Delayed Component, demands that component configurations of delayed which are not used anymore have to be deactivated:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;     If the service registered by a component configuration becomes unused&lt;br/&gt;
     because there are no more bundles using it, then SCR should deactivate that&lt;br/&gt;
     component configuration. This allows SCR implementations to eagerly&lt;br/&gt;
     reclaim activated component configurations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently only component instances created for service factory components are reclaimed when they are not used anymore. Instances of delayed components are not reclaimed at the moment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
